# =============================================================================
# FIREBASE CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# 
# IMPORTANT: Environment Variable Naming Convention
# - Client-side (React app): Use VITE_FIREBASE_* prefix (required by Vite)
# - Server-side (API routes, serverless): Use FIREBASE_* prefix (without VITE_)
# 
# For Vercel/Production:
# - Set BOTH sets of variables in Vercel Environment Variables
# - Client-side: VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY, VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN, etc.
# - Server-side: FIREBASE_API_KEY, FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN, FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL, etc.
#
# How to get these values:
# 1. Go to Firebase Console: https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Select your project (reride-ade6a)
# 3. Go to Project Settings (gear icon) → General tab
# 4. Scroll down to "Your apps" section
# 5. Click on the web app icon (</>) or create a new web app
# 6. Copy the config values
#
# =============================================================================
# CLIENT-SIDE VARIABLES (React/Vite - Required for frontend)
# =============================================================================

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIzaSyDym4_piy6jakV5YAwP9pzaj_iTuNwrJK4
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=reride-ade6a.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=reride-ade6a
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=reride-ade6a.firebasestorage.app
